                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Quires I and II (fols. 2r-9v). The handwriting appears a bit uneven with narrow formed, irregularly slanted and broadly spaced letters; some letters have forked hook vowel markers (esp. ን, ጋ). The handwriting is very similar (possibly identical) to that of Ms. BQM-009.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">Quires III-XVI (fols. 10ra-119rb); wide, broadly spaced, rounded and upright letters.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#00" n="#">Fol. 119rb: Donation note.</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 119rb: This book is of fitawrari Ḫaylu [and] of wäyzäro Ṭǝru who donated it to the tabot of John the Bapitist of Gwälˁa ˀAgame, that it might be for them a guide to the Kingdom of Heaven.</q>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The internal number of the ecclesiastic library has been written on fol. 1r: 5 No 7. 24-8-93 (?)&#xD;
- Stamp of the church on fols. 1r, 3r, 38r, 55r, 119r.&#xD;
- Omissions inserted interlineally: fols. 10vab, 14ra, 19rb, 24ra, 27vb, 31rb, 49va, 60va, 59rb, 97ra, 109rb, 114ra.&#xD;
- Immediate correction indicated by dots around the letter to be cancelled on fol. 16vb.&#xD;
- Erroneously written words crossed out: fols. 68ra, 73ra.&#xD;
- Spaces for names of individuals to be rubricated are left unfilled on fol. 31rb.</item>
                     </list>
